eNCA’s Siphamandla Goge reports. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Who will the next national police commissioner be? That’s the question many are asking following President Cyril Ramaphosa's axing of Khehla Sitole. READ: Sapu: Sitole is a political casualty Sitole’s been plagued by serious allegations of misconduct and a troubled relationship with Police Minister Bheki Cele. Some leadership experts and unions say the new sheriff must have strong leadership qualities to fix the mess within the police and deal decisively with increasing violent crime. eNCA’s Siphamandla Goge reports in the video above.